{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:hebrews.3",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "hebrews",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Hebrews 3 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:1",
      "text": "Wherefore, holy brethren, partakers of the heavenly vocation consider the apostle and high priest of our confession, Jesus:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:2",
      "text": "Who is faithful to him that made him, as was also Moses in all his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:3",
      "text": "For this man was counted worthy of greater glory than Moses, by so much as he that hath built the house hath greater honour than the house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:4",
      "text": "For every house is built by some man: but he that created all things is God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:5",
      "text": "And Moses indeed was faithful in all his house as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were to be said:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:6",
      "text": "But Christ, as the Son in his own house: which house are we, if we hold fast the confidence and glory of hope unto the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:7",
      "text": "Wherefore, as the Holy Ghost saith: To-day if you shall hear his voice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:8",
      "text": "Harden not your hearts, as in the provocation, in the day of temptation in the desert,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:9",
      "text": "Where your fathers tempted me, proved and saw my works,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:10",
      "text": "Forty years: for which cause I was offended with this generation, and I said: They always err in heart. And they have not known my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:11",
      "text": "As I have sworn in my wrath: If they shall enter into my rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:12",
      "text": "Take heed, brethren, lest perhaps there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief, to depart from the living God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:13",
      "text": "But exhort one another every day, whilst it is called to day, that none of you be hardened through the deceitfulness of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:14",
      "text": "For we are made partakers of Christ: yet so, if we hold the beginning of his substance firm unto the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:15",
      "text": "While it is said: To day, if you shall hear his voice, harden not your hearts, as in that provocation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:16",
      "text": "For some who heard did provoke: but not all that came out of Egypt by Moses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:17",
      "text": "And with whom was he offended forty years? Was it not with them that sinned, whose carcasses were overthrown in the desert?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:18",
      "text": "And to whom did he swear, that they should not enter into his rest: but to them that were incredulous?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:hebrews.3.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:19",
      "text": "And we see that they could not enter in, because of unbelief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
